@page "/docviewer"
@rendermode InteractiveWebAssembly
@using BlazorDX.Components

<PageTitle>Document viewer</PageTitle>

<h1>BlazorDX Document Viewer</h1>

<p class="dx-demo-meta">
    One viewer, many formats. <code>DxDocumentViewer</code> dispatches on each
    document's kind: images render with zoom, Markdown through the safe
    <code>DxMarkdown</code> renderer, text/code in a <code>&lt;pre&gt;</code>, and
    PDFs in the browser's native viewer — no bundled PDF engine. Pick a document
    from the sidebar.
</p>

<p class="dx-demo-meta">
    The PDF and image kinds get a keyboard-accessible action toolbar — Download,
    Print, and Open-in-new-tab — with labeled controls that meet the 24&times;24
    target size and show a visible focus ring. The embedded frame carries a
    <code>title</code> (its accessible name), and an explicit download link sits
    below the viewer so assistive-technology users — and browsers with no inline
    PDF plugin — can always get the file.
</p>

<DxDocumentViewer Documents="docs" />

<h2>Toolbar parameters</h2>

<p class="dx-demo-meta">
    The toolbar and each action are individually toggleable
    (<code>ShowToolbar</code>, <code>ShowDownload</code>, <code>ShowPrint</code>,
    <code>ShowOpenInNewTab</code>); all default on. Turning the toolbar off never
    removes the accessible download fallback below the PDF.
</p>

<DxDocumentViewer Documents="pdfOnly" ShowPrint="false" ShowOpenInNewTab="false" />

